notesStmt.note: Many edges and corners of leaves mended with paper.

msContents.summary: An extensive treatise on Aristotelian astronomy, considering the motion of the stars and planets in a spherical, geocentric universe.

supportDesc.extent: 177 leaves : 280 x 215 (220 x 145) mm. bound to 280 x 225 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 175; [1-37, 50-101, 124-145, 145-152, 101-124, 154-185]; modern foliation in pencil, correcting previous foliation in pencil, lower center recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a maghrebi/andalusi script by Aḥmad ibn Aḥmad ibn Salāmah al-[?] Senhadja al-[?], an astronomer (colophon, f. 185r).

binding.p: Morocco, blind-stamped with a medallion and blind- and gilt-tooled, with a flap.

origin.p: Written in Spain in 1381 (f. 154r, 157v, 185r) for Qursunna al-Isrāʼīlī, astronomer to Pedro IV of Aragon (colophon, f. 185r).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Imam Aḥmad ibn Mubārak Lutfullāh, Muḥammad al-Raʼīs and Imam Muḥammad ʻAbd al-Kathīr al-Kinānī (note by Misjo Rinijo, f. 1v).
Formerly owned by Misjo Rinijo (Monsieur Rinillot?), a French ambassador (note dated 1922, f. 1v).
Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, June 1998.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
